## Summary

The Renovate PR [#3501](https://github.com/vexxhost/atmosphere/pull/3501) (and related stable branch Renovate PRs) has been blocked for a while because newer vexxhost images no longer ship the standalone WSGI binary scripts (e.g. `/var/lib/openstack/bin/<service>-wsgi`). Instead, the entry point must be set to the app's Python library module path using the `module` key in the uWSGI config.

This has already been done for some services:
- **nova**: `module: "nova.wsgi.osapi_compute:application"` and `module: "nova.wsgi.metadata:application"` (via `charts/patches/nova/0003-use-wsgi-module-instead-of-script.patch`)
- **cinder**: `module: "cinder.wsgi.api:application"` (via `charts/patches/cinder/0001-tune-uwsgi-config.patch`)

## Services still using `wsgi-file` that need to be updated

The following services still reference a `wsgi-file` path and need to be migrated to a `module` entrypoint:

| Service | Current `wsgi-file` value | Expected `module` value |
|---|---|---|
| **octavia** | `/var/lib/openstack/bin/octavia-wsgi` | `octavia.api.wsgi:application` (or equivalent) |
| **designate** | `/var/lib/openstack/bin/designate-api-wsgi` | `designate.api.wsgi:application` (or equivalent) |
| **neutron** (api) | `/var/lib/openstack/bin/neutron-api` | `neutron.server.wsgi:application` (or equivalent) |
| **neutron** (policy server) | `/var/lib/openstack/bin/neutron-policy-server-wsgi` | TBD |
| **placement** | `/var/lib/openstack/bin/placement-api` | `placement.wsgi:init_application` (or equivalent) |
| **barbican** | (via `/etc/barbican/barbican-api-uwsgi.ini`) | TBD |
| **manila** | (via `/etc/manila/manila-api-uwsgi.ini`) | TBD |
| **magnum** | (via `/etc/magnum/magnum-api-uwsgi.ini`) | `magnum.api.app:create_wsgi_app` — see open PR [#3724](https://github.com/vexxhost/atmosphere/pull/3724) |
| **ironic** | TBD | TBD |
| **keystone** | (uses Apache2 / cgi-bin copy) | may need review |
| **ovn network logging parser** | `/var/lib/openstack/bin/neutron-ovn-network-logging-parser-wsgi` | TBD |

> Note: Glance already has its own patching — please verify its status as well.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Each affected service chart has a patch (or inline values override) replacing `wsgi-file` with the correct `module: "<python.module.path>:application"` entry in its uWSGI config
- [ ] The Renovate PR #3501 (main branch) and equivalent stable-branch Renovate PRs are unblocked and pass CI after the fix
- [ ] No regression in service startup for already-working services

